    "summary": " Influenced by Max Weber, \u00c9mile Durkheim, Marcel Mauss, Karl Marx, Bronis\u0142aw Malinowski, Thorstein Veblen, Pierre Bourdieu, Erving Goffman, E. E. Evans-Pritchard, Peter L. Berger, Mary Douglas, Edward Said, Bruno Latour, Sidney Mintz, George Marcus, James Ferguson, Taussig, Peter Pels, Peter Geschiere, Daniel Miller, Charles Stewart, Michael Herzfeld, Akis Papataxiarchis, Dimitra Gefou-Madianou. \nI continue working on social and cultural anthropology, ethnography and materiality in Greece (modernity, consumption, migration, religion and death) and I am currently expanding my research on the uses-meaning of Umbanda in Brazil. I am interested in various types of cults, especially Exu and Pomba Gira, and I hope to contribute to a visual and written ethnography of the entities, their relationship to humans or non-humans and the ways that they relate to the local identity of Rio.",
