            "title": "Super-diversity and the rise of the far right in the city of Athens",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 9,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2013
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": null,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": null
                }
            },
            "description": "In order to understand the causes of the emergence of the far right and its masking of diversity, the main research question examines the uses of \u201cimmigration\u201d and \u201cdiversity\u201d in public and official discourse including the Greek Orthodox Church, the social policy and the public manifestations of cultural difference. A major part of the research focuses on the \u201crepresentations of diversity\u201d and how these imaginaries affect or legitimize neonazism and the emergence of the far right. Furthermore in order to examine the consequences of super diversity the research draws a detailed ethnography of the reception of the far right in the city of\nAthens by examining the encounters between \u2018locals\u2019 and \u2018immigrants\u2019 in a number of inter- group contacts and social relationships in key public spaces. How is the social life of immigrants affected by active members of far right networks or other ultra nationalists? How do these networks organize pogroms or other racist attacks? How is the social geography/ public space of Athens affected? What strategies and tactics do people use in these encounters?",
