                    "company": "Leiden University",
                    "description": "During my PhD, I worked on a historical ethnography of whisky consumption on Skyros island and the center of Athens and I was able to trace the expansion of the transnational conglomerates in post authoritarian Greece. I looked at how cultural practices accommodated Scotch in the everyday life of laborers, shepherds and young professionals in island and urban Greece and how Scotch became a materialization of modernity and masculine styles.  My PhD research has been published by Berghahn under the title: Greek whisky: The localization of a global commodity (Oxford & New York).",
